content.rendered:
Lamborghini Club Indonesia has held quite a few evens and tours in 2018 such as the Cirebon – Bandung touring as well as the Central Java tour. To kick off the new year, LCI decided to take its cars out of Java and onto the Island of The Gods. 

The tour commenced from the 15th – 19th of February 2019. Meaning, 3 full days of jam packed Lamborghini fun in Bali

After landing in Bali, eager to get on the road and enjoy what Bali has to offer, the first stop we had to visit was Omnia Beach Club, with all the Lamborghini’s cruising together and seeing them at the venue was something else. Beach clubs and Laborghini’s? What more could you ask for. 

Ater touring around Bali for a few days and enjoying the scenery, we made a stop at an iconic destination which was Garuda Wisnu Kencana (GWK). This was a place we had to visit as it’s one of the most iconic symbols in Bali, gaining access to drive right up to the foot of the structure.

Enjoy more of the photos from the tour!
